{"source_key":"sha256-a153ef5d901086d9225a50321b8764ab","record_index":334,"record_hash":"sha256:0685258325243f228daddb8cfc48c02c80ce0b5e42cff611b615895b09b4ae0c","timestamp":"2026-05-15T19:11:15.099Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"That confirms it: the culprit is the new graph-backed base branch resolver.\n\nThose errors are from [base.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/gitbutler-branch-actions/src/base.rs:350):\n\n- `target_to_base_branch require a defined target_ref`\n- `target_to_base_branch require a defined target_commit_id`\n\nIn 0.19.11, `target_to_base_branch()` reads those from projected `ws`, not the persisted workspace metadata. So users likely still have a configured base branch, but the current projected workspace sometimes lacks target data. Then [virtual_branches.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-api/src/legacy/virtual_branches.rs:289) swallows the error into `Ok(None)`, and the UI sends them to setup. Pretty nasty little trap.\n\nThe fix I’d make: stop using strict projection-only fields for base branch identity.\n\nUse the fallback helpers that already exist:\n\n- `ws.target_ref_name()` instead of `ws.target_ref.as_ref()`\n- `ws.target_base_commit_id()` instead of `ws.target_commit_id()`\n\nAnd for `current_sha`, if `ws.target_ref_tip_commit_id()` is missing, fall back to `repo.find_reference(target_ref_name)?.peel_to_commit()?.id`.\n\nBigger principle: `get_base_branch_data` should use persisted target metadata as source of truth for “is base branch configured?” and use graph projection only for derived niceties like upstream commits. Projection failure should not make the app pretend setup never happened.\n\nI’d also change the API swallow behavior: only return `Ok(None)` for a real “no configured target” case. For these projection errors, log/return the error so the UI doesn’t route to setup and nuke user confidence.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-15T19:11:15.099Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}